The paper deals with the classic problem of makespan minimization on unrelated machines, which is a well-studied problem in approximation algorithms and falls under the category of Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM) and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also uses LP relaxation and rounding techniques, which are common in the field of Computational Complexity (cs.CC). The paper also discusses the integrality gap, which is a concept in Linear Programming and falls under the category of Linear Algebra (cs.LG). Finally, the paper discusses the hardness of approximation, which is a topic in the field of Graph Theory (cs.GT).
